This derivative modifies the original. Notable changes:
  - Invert the recommendation flow: the user answers first and the skill
    steel-mans then pushes back, instead of the skill leading with its
    recommended answer (avoids anchoring the user).
  - Restructure the single prose paragraph into explicit sections:
    How to ask / How to recommend / When to stop.
  - Add AskUserQuestion guidance — use multiple choice when a branch has
    2-4 plausible answers.
  - Add stop criteria plus a decision-summary and an opt-in persist-to-file step.
  - Rename to ultra-decision-griller and broaden the description to trigger on
    intent across languages.

The core concept and several phrasings (relentless one-branch-at-a-time
interviewing, "explore the codebase instead") are carried from the original.
